        <h2>Part 5: Test &amp; Iterate (1 hour)</h2>

        <h3>Step 17: Test Your Infrastructure</h3>
        <pre><code class="language-bash"># Create short URL
curl -X POST $API_ENDPOINT/shorten \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"url": "https://terraform.io"}'

# Test redirect
curl -I $API_ENDPOINT/abc123

# Check stats
curl $API_ENDPOINT/stats/abc123</code></pre>

        <p><strong>It works!</strong> And you did it all with Terraform.</p>

        <h3>Step 18: Make Changes and Re-deploy</h3>
        <p>Try changing something:</p>
        <pre><code class="language-terraform"># In main.tf, change Lambda memory
resource "aws_lambda_function" "shorten" {
  # ... other config
  memory_size = 512  # Changed from 256
}</code></pre>

        <pre><code class="language-bash"># See what will change
terraform plan

# Apply changes
terraform apply</code></pre>

        <p><strong>Terraform only updates what changed!</strong> This is the power of IaC.</p>
